# Clean Dark Mode Overhaul

The current dark mode looks "muddy" because: (1) many components have **zero** dark variants (Appointments, Inventory, Calendar, DashboardActions, chart cards), (2) those that do use inconsistent `gray-700`, `gray-800`, and `gray-900` shades with no clear hierarchy, and (3) the `card-shell` utility class only has a single dark style with no depth tokens.

The fix is to establish a **single coherent dark palette** based on `zinc` tones (which are neutral and crisp compared to `gray`) and sweep every component with it.

## Proposed Dark Palette

| Role | Token | Hex |
|---|---|---|
| Page background | `zinc-950` | `#09090b` |
| Card / panel surface | `zinc-900` | `#18181b` |
| Elevated surface (inner cards, inputs) | `zinc-800` | `#27272a` |
| Border | `zinc-700` | `#3f3f46` |
| Primary text | `zinc-50` | `#fafafa` |
| Secondary text | `zinc-400` | `#a1a1aa` |
| Muted text | `zinc-500` | `#71717a` |

---

## Proposed Changes

### Foundation

#### [MODIFY] [tailwind.config.js](file:///c:/Users/Gabrielle/OneDrive/Desktop/AUTOVET/tailwind.config.js)
- Add a `dark` color alias set pointing to `zinc` shades so we can use semantic tokens like `dark:bg-dark-card`.
- Keep `darkMode: "class"` as-is.

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Gabrielle/OneDrive/Desktop/AUTOVET/src/index.css)
- Change body dark background from `gray-900` → `zinc-950`.
- Update `.card-shell` dark variant from `gray-800` → `zinc-900` and border to `zinc-700`.
- Add a `.input-dark` utility for form inputs.

